Polish Soccer Division to Name Broadcaster Tomorrow, Gazeta Says

-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 
2011-02-13T12:59:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/polish-soccer-division-to-name-broadcaster-tomorrow-gazeta-says.html
Ekstraklasa, Poland’s top soccer
division, will choose a broadcaster tomorrow to televise its
games for the next three years, Gazeta Wyborcza  reported on its
website , without citing anyone.  N, the satellite broadcaster owned by  TVN SA , Poland’s only
publicly traded television network, bid for the rights,
according to Gazeta. So did competitor Canal Plus, controlled by  Vivendi SA , it said. Ekstraklasa values the TV rights at 420
million zloty ($145 million) over the three-year period, Gazeta
reported, without saying where it got the information.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maciej Martewicz in Warsaw at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  